Welcome to Mika(the “Platform”). The Platform is provided and controlled by Mika Team. (“Mika”, “we” or “us”). We are committed to protecting and respecting your privacy. This Privacy Policy covers the experience we provide for users age 1
8
and over on our Platform.
The Privacy Policy was written in English (US). To the extent any translated version of this agreement conflicts with the English version, the English version controls.
The full legal bit
We know that other people’s use of your personal data is a big concern for social network users, so we have developed this privacy policy (the "Policy") to let you know how we use personal data (“personal data”).
Our Policy applies to your use of the Mika. We suggest you read it in conjunction with our
Terms and Conditions of Use
(the “Terms”). When you access or use Mika, you agree to our Privacy Policy and you consent to our collection, storage, use and disclosure of your personal data as we’ve set out in this Policy.
Mika reserves the right to change our Policy at any time and without notice, so be sure to check this Policy regularly to understand how we use your data.
By installing, using, registering to or otherwise accessing the services, you agree to this privacy policy and give an explicit and informed consent to the processing of your personal data in accordance with this privacy policy.
IF YOU DO NOT ACCEPT AND AGREE WITH OUR PRIVACY POLICY THEN YOU MUST NOT ACCESS OR USE THE APP.
The Summary
If you clicked through to here from our Terms and Conditions of Use. You should read this privacy policy because it will tell you exactly how your personal data is being looked after by Mika and that’s a pretty important thing for you to know. Here are the topics that we cover:
i.
What Data do We Collect
We collect and process data you give us when you create an account and upload content to the Platform.
ii.
How We Use Your Data
We use your data to provide the Platform to you and to improve and administer it. We use your data to, among other things, show you suggestions in the ‘For You’ feed, improve and develop the Platform and ensure your safety.
iii.
Data Storage
We will recognize and retain your data within India territory for as long as it is necessary to provide you with the service. When we do not need your data in order to provide the service to you, we retain it only as long as we have a legitimate business purpose in keeping such data or where we are subject to a legal obligation to retain the data. We will also retain your data if we believe it is or will be necessary for the establishment, exercise or defense of legal claims.
iv.
Change
We will generally notify all users of any material changes to this policy, through a notice provided via the Platform.
However, you should look at this policy regularly to check for any changes. We will also update the “Last Updated” date at the top of this policy, which reflects the effective date of such policy. Your continued access to or use of the Platform after the date of the updated policy constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy. If you do not agree to the updated policy, you must stop accessing or using the Platform.
I.
What data do we collect
We collect data when you create an account and use the Platform. We also collect technical and behavioral data about your use of the Platform. We also collect data contained in the messages you send through our Platform
.
More data about the categories and sources of data is provided below.
Data you choose to provide
For certain activities, such as when you register, upload content to the Platform, make broadcast or contact us directly, you may provide some or all of the following data:
•
Registration data, such as age, username and password, language, and email or phone number
•
Profile data, such as name and profile image
•
User-generated content, including comments, photographs, and virtual item videos that you choose to upload or broadcast on the Platform (“User Content”)
•
Payment data, such as PayPal or other third-party payment data (where required for the purpose of payment)
•
Your opt-in choices and communication preferences
•
Data to verify an account
•
Data in correspondence you send to us
For safety and security and to ensure you have the best possible user experience, we require users to verify their accounts (because we want to make sure you are not a robot!) and might ask for your phone number. Don’t worry! This is only to make sure you are real and breathing! We won't use your phone number for marketing purposes.
Data we collect automatically
Once you have created a Profile, you may choose to edit your gender, birthday and other data. Moreover, we will automatically track certain data such as your IP, device data (model, system, MCC), timezone. And we also collect data about mobile operators, network data (4G\3G\WIFI). That data helps us identify your physical location so that you can
use
"nearby"
function
to check other users and moments.
When you use our Service, your position, microphone and phone camera shall be used upon your explicit authorization, the certain log file data shall be uploaded by yourself. All such data allows for more accurate reporting and improvement of the Service.
Data we obtain from other sources
We may receive the data described in this Privacy Policy from other sources, such as:
Third-Party Services.
We may collect data about you from third-party services, such as advertising partners, payment partners and analytics providers.
II. How do we use your data
We will use your data to fulfill and enforce our Terms and Conditions of Use , to improve our Platform and customize your ad experience, we may use your data that we received to:
1. help you efficiently access your data after you sign in;
2. remember data so you will not have to re-enter it during your visit or the next time you visit the Service;
3. provide personalized content and data to you and others, which could include customized content, online ads or other forms of marketing;
4. provide, improve, test, and monitor the effectiveness of our Service;
5. develop and test new products and features;
6. monitor metrics such as total number of visitors, traffic, and demographic patterns;
7. diagnose or fix technology problems,
to fulfill requests for products, services, Platform functionality, support and data for internal operations, including troubleshooting, data analysis, testing, research, statistical, and survey purposes and to solicit your feedback;
8. help us detect abuse, fraud, and illegal activity on the Platform
